NUMBER=1216,
PAGES=4,
DAY=3,
MONTH=mar,
YEAR=1991,
ABSTRACT="The history of computer communication contains many examples
of efforts to align the capabilities of processors to that of
communication media. Packet switching is the classic case of a careful
