ABSTRACT="by host groups may not address the requirements of those
researchers who are building fault tolerant software. Our basic premise
is that reliable handling of failures, recoveries, and dynamic process
migration are important aspects of programming in distributed
environments, and that communication support that provides unpredictable
behavior in the presence of such events places an unacceptable burden of
complexity on higher level application software. This complexity does
not arise when using the fault-tolerant process group alternative.",
URL="ftp://ftp.isi.edu/in-notes/rfc992.txt",
}

